 350 years ago stands as an extraordinary historical achievement. And the implications of his study are equally important: are we adequately prepared—or even preparing—for the catastrophes that climate change brings?  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aCivil warxHistoryx17th century. 0aCivil warxHistoryy17th century. 0aClimatic changesxSocial aspectsxHistoryx17th century. 0aClimatic changesxSocial aspectsxHistoryy17th century. 0aDisastersxHistoryx17th century. 0aDisastersxHistoryy17th century. 0aHistory, Modernx17th century. 0aHistory, Moderny17th century. 0aMilitary historyx17th century. 0aMilitary historyy17th century. 0aRevolutionsxHistoryx17th century. 0aRevolutionsxHistoryy17th century. 7aHISTORY / World.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311053799440uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030018919340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300189193423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300189193/original  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles